# Icon Usage

## Import

```typescript
import { Icon, createIcon } from '@oxymormon/chg-unified-ds';
```

## Usage

```tsx
// Standalone
<Icon name="copy" size={24} />
<Icon name="check" className="text-red-500" />

// In Button
<Button iconLeading={({ className }) => <Icon name="copy" className={className} />}>
  Copy
</Button>

// Icon-only Button (no children)
<Button 
  iconLeading={({ className }) => <Icon name="copy" className={className} />}
  aria-label="Copy to clipboard"
/>

// With createIcon helper
const CopyIcon = createIcon('copy');
<Button iconLeading={CopyIcon}>Copy</Button>
```

## Adding New Icons

1. Find icon at [phosphoricons.com](https://phosphoricons.com)
2. Add to `src/components/Icon/Icon.tsx`:
   ```typescript
   import { ArrowRight } from '@phosphor-icons/react';
   
   const icons = {
     // ... existing
     'arrow-right': ArrowRight, // PascalCase → kebab-case
   } as const;
   ```
3. TypeScript auto-updates `IconName` type

## Naming Convention

- `ArrowRightIcon` → `arrow-right`
- `ChevronDownIcon` → `chevron-down`
- `SignOutIcon` → `sign-out`

**Rule**: PascalCase → kebab-case, drop "Icon" suffix

## Props

- `name: IconName` - Required
- `size?: number | string` - Icon size
- `weight?: 'thin' | 'light' | 'regular' | 'bold' | 'fill' | 'duotone'` - Default: 'regular'
- `color?: string` - Default: 'currentColor' (inherits from parent)
- `className?: string` - Tailwind classes work via currentColor

## Available Icons

`copy`, `check`, `chevron-down`, `caret-down`, `sign-out`, `trash`, `plus`, `clock-counter-clockwise`, `sliders`
